Sentencas: Cobalt-free composites Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-delta (NSFCu)-xSm(0.2)Ce(0.8)O(1.9) (SDC) (x = 0-60 wt %) are investigated as IT-SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ-xSm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cobalt-free composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The characteristic properties of cobalt-free composite cathodes comparing to cobalt-based composites are revealed.
Titulo: Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ-xSm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cobalt-free composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The DC conductivity and thermal expansion coefficient of the composite cathodes decrease with the content of SDC x, while the polarization resistance R-p shows the least value with addition of 40 wt% of SDC.
Titulo: Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ-xSm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cobalt-free composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The power density of the single cell with NSFCu-40% SDC composite cathode improved significantly compared with that of undoped NSFCu cathode, with peak values of 488, 623, 849 and 1052 mW cm(-2) at 600, 650, 700, and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ-xSm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cobalt-free composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Moreover, the performance of the composite cathode is stable within testing period of 370 h at 700 degrees C, indicating that the NSECu-40% SDC is an excellent cobalt-free composite cathode applied in IT-SOFC.
Titulo: Nd0.5Sr0.5Fe0.8Cu0.2O3-δ-xSm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 cobalt-free composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
